Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (South Ionian) pottery cup; offset of lip just preserved at top; clay very micaceous; glaze fired red-brown; interior glazed; exterior reserved except for a band at top of wall; inscription cut on exterior, in reserved zone.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.852)
